# Common Care Editorial Profile Pattern

When asked to "apply CC Editorial Profile" or "reuse AboutTabs style", follow this pattern.

- Use semantic headings first (`h1`..`h5`) and let global type scale drive size.
- For paragraph copy, prefer plain `p` (global body rhythm) unless `care-body` is explicitly needed for scoped care-page rhythm.
- Keep vertical rhythm restrained: use 80px section breaks for major transitions and 24-40px for local spacing.
- Use calm, editorial containers: `max-w-[1400px]` page shell with readable inner columns (`max-w-3xl` / `max-w-2xl`).
- For profile rows, use left image + right text with `55/45` or `60/40` split and centered alignment.
- Use subtle surfaces only (`bg-bone` / `bg-background`), hairline borders, soft radius, minimal shadows.
- Avoid heavy UI chrome (no loud cards, no aggressive outlines, no dark utility panels unless explicitly requested).

## Reusable Section Structure

1. Headline block (semantic heading + short intro)
2. Optional contained full-width image (within page container, not edge-to-edge unless requested)
3. Profile/content rows with semantic heading + global body paragraphs
4. Optional compact link row/CTA

## Navigation Drawer Style

- Prefer contained hover drawers (roughly 320-420px), anchored to nav item.
- Keep links curated and concise; avoid full-width mega panels and teaser columns.
- Motion: subtle fade + tiny vertical shift only.
